## What
Create src/docs/TopicSection.svelte that renders a single topic with its demos and markdown body.

## Why
This is the core rendering component. Given a topic object, it renders:
1. Title as h3 with anchor id
2. Summary paragraph
3. Each demo via CodeExample (live preview + syntax-highlighted code)
4. Markdown body content

## Implementation
Create src/docs/TopicSection.svelte:

```svelte
<script lang="ts">
  import CodeExample from './CodeExample.svelte';
  import { getDemo } from './demos/registry';
  import SvelteMarkdown from '@humanspeak/svelte-markdown';

  interface Topic {
    id: string;
    title: string;
    summary: string;
    whenToUse: string;
    classes: string[];
    demos: string[];
    markdown: string;
  }

  interface Props {
    topic: Topic;
  }

  let { topic }: Props = $props();
</script>

<section class="stack" id={topic.id}>
  <h3>{topic.title}</h3>
  <p>{topic.summary}</p>

  {#if topic.classes.length > 0}
    <p class="fs-xs text-muted">
      <strong>Classes:</strong> {topic.classes.join(', ')}
    </p>
  {/if}

  {#each topic.demos as demoName}
    {#await getDemo(demoName) then demo}
      {#if demo}
        {#await Promise.all([demo.component(), demo.code()]) then [mod, code]}
          <CodeExample code={code} title={demoName}>
            <mod.default />
          </CodeExample>
        {/await}
      {/if}
    {/await}
  {/each}

  <div class="topic-content">
    <SvelteMarkdown source={topic.markdown} />
  </div>
</section>
```

## Verification
- Import TopicSection in a test page
- Pass a topic object from runtime.js
- Verify title, summary, demos, and markdown all render
- Verify demo code is syntax-highlighted

## Dependencies
- Task 1 (demo registry) must be complete

## Files
- CREATE: src/docs/TopicSection.svelte

## What
Create src/docs/demos/registry.ts that auto-discovers all demo components and provides lazy imports for both the component and raw code.

## Why
Topics reference demos by name (e.g., demos: ['Buttons']). We need a way to resolve 'Buttons' to:
1. The Buttons.svelte component (for live rendering)
2. The raw source code (for CodeExample display)

## Implementation
Create src/docs/demos/registry.ts:

```typescript
// Auto-generate registry from all demo files
const demoModules = import.meta.glob('./*.svelte');
const demoRawModules = import.meta.glob('./*.svelte', { query: '?raw', import: 'default' });

export interface DemoEntry {
  component: () => Promise<{ default: any }>;
  code: () => Promise<string>;
}

export const demoRegistry: Record<string, DemoEntry> = {};

for (const path of Object.keys(demoModules)) {
  // Extract name: './Buttons.svelte' -> 'Buttons'
  const name = path.replace('./', '').replace('.svelte', '');
  demoRegistry[name] = {
    component: demoModules[path] as () => Promise<{ default: any }>,
    code: demoRawModules[path] as () => Promise<string>,
  };
}

export function getDemo(name: string): DemoEntry | undefined {
  return demoRegistry[name];
}

export function hasDemo(name: string): boolean {
  return name in demoRegistry;
}
```

## Verification
- Import registry in a test file
- Verify getDemo('Buttons') returns component and code loaders
- Verify hasDemo('NonExistent') returns false
- Verify all 40 existing demos are registered

